"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-06-olympic-pole-vaulter-offered-250-000-porn-deal-going-viral-paris-games-21369598\", \"text\": \"Anthony Ammirati has been offered a porn deal worth $250,000 after the French pole vaulter went viral at the 2024Olympic GamesinParis.  Ammirati sentsocial mediainto a frenzy with an infamous attempt at clearing 5.70 meters, withhis penis getting right in the wayto cost him a spot in the final.  The 21-year-old pole vaulting star now has the opportunity toturn that heartbreakinto cash, with pornographic website CamSoda making him a big financial offer.  CamSoda vice president Daryn Parker toldTMZ: 'If it was up to me, I'd award [Anthony Ammirati] for what everyone else saw, [his] talent below the belt.  Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  'As a lover of crotch-centric activities, I'd love to offer you up to $250,000 in exchange for a 60-minute webcam show, in which you show off your goods, minus the crossbar, of course.'  Ammirati finished 12th in his group, unable to book a spot in the pole vault final, which would have given him a shot at landing an Olympic medal at his home Games.  'It's a big disappointment,' the Frenchman said after his elimination. 'I am a bit gutted, because I did not miss anything on the third attempt at 5.70m.  'What I did miss was a bit of jumping in training to fine-tune the settings. Just a technical session.  'I had to give up the last two, because after a small grade one in the adductor, I prioritised the race. I was 100 per cent physically, but I was missing a bit\\u2026  'The conditions were good. It's the first time I have started a competition without any stress. As I was a total outsider, I only had one goal: to play with the public. I was almost there.'  Serena Williams' former coach Rennae Stubbs has offered some advice for Ammirati and has urged him to 'call a drag queen' for his future events.  'My man!' Stubbs posted on X. 'Call a drag queen! She will teach u how to tuck it! This is unbelievable!  Tucking is generally referred to as\\u00a0hiding the genitals between the legs and buttocks, to create a flat pelvic area.  ArrowMORE:Why does one volleyball player wear a different colour at the Olympics?  ArrowMORE:Why do women wear headguards but not men in Olympic boxing?  ArrowMORE:Adam Peaty reveals grim Olympic Village catering; says 'worms' are found in food  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"